BitStamp.net
A bitcoin [[currency_exchange]] accepting deposits in

* EUR
* USD
* CHF


The service was announced August 21, 2011 (1.1). BitStamp.net is owned by BitStamp d.o.o. Slovenian based company.

##Trading

* Buying/selling

A buy/sell order is executed partially or in full when the price bid can be matched against a sell/buy order that is at or below the bid amount. 

##Adding funds

* BTC
There are no fees incurred when when transferring bitcoins for deposit. Funds are available once confirmed (6 confirms), a process that can take roughly one hour.

* USD
Exchange accepts international wire transfers in USD

* EUR
Exchange accepts EUR deposits via SEPA transfers, then converts them to USD and credits them to online account.
SEPA deposits must go through additional step of converting funds to USD, which can in some cases delay deposit for additional day

* CHF
Exchange accepts CHF  transfers, then converts them to USD and credits them to online account.
CHF deposits must go through additional step of converting funds to USD, which can in some cases delay deposit for additional day

##Fees
BitStamp charges a trading fee of up to 0.5% from each party of successful trades made through the market. The fee appears in the account history next to each trade.

##Withdrawing funds

* BTC
Bitcoins may be withdrawn at no charge.

* USD
International withdrawals will be charged with 0.09% fee, minimum fee is $15,00. Minimum amount for international withdrawal is $50,00.

* EUR
SEPA withdrawals are charged with fixed 0.90€ fee once your funds are converted to EUR. Minimum amount for SEPA withdrawal is $10,00.

* CHF
CHF withdrawals are charged with fixed 0.90€ fee once your funds are converted to EUR. Minimum amount for SEPA withdrawal is $10,00.

